    "process_code": "PROC-EXP-001",
    "process_name": "Employee Expense Reimbursement",
    "process_overview": "The Employee Expense Reimbursement process governs how Meridian Retail Group employees submit and receive reimbursement for approved business expenses. An employee submits an expense report with receipts, a finance clerk verifies the receipts against policy, and a single exclusive gateway routes the request to either payment processing or rejection. Approved claims are paid by the payroll officer and archived by the finance clerk; rejected claims are routed to an HR coordinator who notifies the employee.",
